-- Kokusai Global Fund Cuts Investment in Euro Government Bonds, Nikkei Says
-- Tak Kumakura
-- 2010-07-13T23:14:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/kokusai-global-fund-cuts-investment-in-euro-government-bonds-nikkei-says.html

          
          
             Kokusai Asset Management Co.’s
Global Sovereign Open cut the proportion of its euro-denominated
government bonds to 25 percent from 42 percent, Nikkei English
News reported, without saying where it obtained the information.  
 Global Sovereign isn’t the only Japanese mutual fund that’s
selling euro-denominated assets. Mitsubishi UFJ Asset Management
Co. last month sold all the Greek bonds that had been managed by
its investment trusts, the report said.  
          
          


  


        